# id: LanguageTestSupport -> protected void assertExpression(String expressionText, String expectedValue, String orThisExpectedValue)
commentText: Asserts that the expression evaluates to one of the two given values
codeText: protected void assertExpression(String expressionText, String expectedValue, String orThisExpectedValue) {_        Language language = assertResolveLanguage(getLanguageName())___        Expression expression = language.createExpression(expressionText)__        assertNotNull("No Expression could be created for text: " + expressionText + " language: " + language, expression)___        Object value__        if (expectedValue != null) {_            value = expression.evaluate(exchange, expectedValue.getClass())__        } else {_            value = expression.evaluate(exchange, Object.class)__        }__        log.debug("Evaluated expression: " + expression + " on exchange: " + exchange + " result: " + value)___        assertTrue("Expression: " + expression + " on Exchange: " + exchange,_                   expectedValue.equals(value) || orThisExpectedValue.equals(value))__    }
